{"subjectName":"Business","subjectDescription":"Discover a full suite of online business courses that will allow you to make better business decisions and succeed in today's competitive business world. Our courses provide a rich learning experience that will allow you to develop critical business skills in areas such as business... Read more...","subjectBg":"https://cdn01.alison-static.net/search/header-img/business.jpg","resumeLink":"https://alison.com/resume/courses/4743","title":"Leading Organizational Development","totalEnrolled":"-","courseIncludes":["Hours of Learning","CPD Accreditation","Final Assessment"],"headline":"Master the key skills required to develop and manage an organization in this free online business course.","description":"How do organizations evolve and progress? What practices, systems and techniques can be used to implement change? Master the concepts of organizational development and management effectively in this exciting business course to create a dynamic work culture. You will gain insight into the different structures, models, enterprise dynamics and group dynamics involved in implementing the most appropriate and visionary changes across your business.","courseOutcomes":["-","-","-","-","-","-","-","-"],"courseDescription":"<p>As businesses develop and the environment changes, strategic development and evolution are critical to long-term success. How should this organizational development be guided and nurtured for the best outcomes? This course is designed to guide you through the concepts and strategies involved in this field. We will begin by exploring the typical management structures that define and govern the relationships between the various employees, their tasks, roles, responsibilities and authority provided to carry out different tasks.&nbsp;</p><p>Next, the course will present how to handle different customer styles and complaints. You will learn about the business basics, innovation and continuous improvement with an insight into the dynamic system. All the top-performing institutions that we know today share a common element in their success: they all have an enterprise strategy. For this reason, we will also discuss the enterprise strategy, resources, change and communication.</p><p>Finally, you will delve into group dynamics: how to create groups, their structure and which strategies follow in their functioning. This course will discuss the cohesiveness and development phases of a group and group socialisation. So upgrade your skills and start this exciting organizational development course today.</p><a href=\"\" class=\"l-but course_btn\"> Start Course Now </a>","certificateDetail":"<p> All Alison courses are free to enrol study and complete. To successfully complete this <span class=\"course-type\"></span> course and become an Alison Graduate, you need to achieve 80% or higher in each course assessment. Once you have completed this <span class=\"course-type\"></span> course, you have the option to acquire an official Diploma, which is a great way to share your achievement with the world. </p><div class=\"l-list l-list--tick\"><h6>Your Alison <span class=\"course-type\"></span> is:</h6><ul><li>Ideal for sharing with potential employers</li><li>Include it in your CV, professional social media profiles and job applications.</li><li>An indication of your commitment to continuously learn, upskill &amp; achieve high results.</li><li>An incentive for you to continue empowering yourself through lifelong learning.</li></ul></div><hr><div class=\"l-flex l-flex--even\"><div class=\"l-list l-list--bullet\"><h6>Alison offers <span class=\"l-list__color\">3 types</span> of Diplomas for completed Diploma courses:</h6><ul><li><strong>Digital <span class=\"course-type\"></span>:</strong> a downloadable <span class=\"course-type\"></span> in PDF format immediately available to you when you complete your purchase. </li><li><strong><span class=\"course-type\"></span>:</strong> a physical version 